history.text: What's the title of the movie?
Jaws
Have you seen it before?
Steven Speilberg did an amazing job directing.
Yes I have.
Me too. It's been a while though.
The acting was amazing,
I man eating shark has always been a fear of mine.
Me too. Anytime I sit in a boat my brain just starts playing the Jaws theme.
Didn't you think Roy Scheider did an amazing job as chief Brody?
Yeah, his acting was really believable.
Have you watched any of the other Jaws movies?
Oh and the scene where the skinny dipping woman was pulled under, it is one of those never forget movie moments.
No not since the original.
Yeah that scene is definitely meant to be burned in a movie watcher's brain.
The funniest part is it was the most cheerful scary movie ever.
And you should try watching Jaws 2. I'd argue that it's even better than the first movie, though it's a bit slow at the beginning.
And yeah, I was surprised at how upbeat it was for a movie about man eating sharks.
I love how real it is portrayed. I can totally see govn people lying to keep a beach open at the holiday.
To say they caught the shark even though no remains were found in it.
Yeah, stuff like that happens all the time. They're people who'd say or do anything if it meant they could get more money.
I always felt bad for Brody's son Micheal in the movie, he was tortured by the events.
Yeah, if you ever get around to watching the sequels, you can really see how traumatized he is by everything that happened.
Major Larry was such a jerk.
I will have to try them.
I will never understand the boat they took Orca to hunt the shark.  It never seemed adequate.
You should absolutely watch Jaws 2, but Jaws 3 made me root for the sharks.
And I will never understand why Hopper went into that shark cage.
Exactly! That boat looked like it would split into 2  if a butterfly landed on it.
And I guess people like Hopper love the thrill, but I'd never be able to go into a rusty looking shark cage like that.
Still one of my favorite bad guy death seens, the scuba tank in the sharks mouth boom.
Never, I rather never go swimming again then get into that cage.
That was really clever. If I was about to get eaten by a shark I wouldn't be able to think anything other than AAAAAAAH!
I would have been in a total panic paddling back to Amity.  Wouldn't have cared if I saw the shark die I would be worried about others.
HAHA AAAAAAHHHHHH is right.
It's good that he kept his cool. I'd probably die of a heart attack before the shark even opened its mouth.
Hooper was certainly the lucky dog though.
Yup
Was Chief Brody in the next movie.
It is funny having my kids watch it, they look and say what awful affects, but for that time it was amazing.
Yeah, and honestly everyone in the town would probably be shark food if not for the Chief.
Was Major Larry in the next one as well?
And I'm pretty young, but I can still appreciate that the effects were good for its time.
They critiqued it as too gruesome for any aged children back then, haha kids now would chuckle compared to what they see now.
Yeah, he comes back for the sequel.
Hard to believe it was created in 1975, didn't know it was done that long before I was born.
I'm surprised that kids today aren't scarred for life with some of the shows they somehow watch(probably behind their parents' backs).
Ya know.
Yeah it looks pretty good for a movie that's over 40 years old.
Absolutely, I have certainly seen worse.
Woody Allen has been killing the movie biz for a long time.
Yeah, and he's still going
I think he played a character in Antz, but I haven't seen that movie since kindergarten, so my memory's a bit fuzzy.
The directing was amazing, to say that some of the scariest parts where scenes that you could even see the shark is impressive.
It really was! I love it when movies can scare you without having to resort to cheap jumpscares.
Absolutely just organic scares and thrills.
It's been fun taking with you! But I gotta go get stuff done. Bye!
